-------------------------

obexg | 2019-07-13 14:56:35 UTC | #22

Hey! One question, why can‚Äôt we use tone anymore?

-------------------------

iammane | 2019-07-13 14:58:30 UTC | #23

You don‚Äôt - I should say you don‚Äôt automate them any more unless they are available controls. Every sound has different controls. Flamingo for example has these:

![image|549x500](upload://4U752bwKmiMiLSsC0YEciI9M2xA.jpeg) ![image|690x486](upload://38OI4iwgQzKxCMA1AnKwdT6SYiC.jpeg) 

So because the instrument has shape and tone, you can automate shape, tone and pitch. For an instrument that no longer has shape or tone, like Boulevard under vintage keys, you only automate pitch.

-------------------------

obexg | 2019-07-13 15:02:25 UTC | #24

But why can‚Äôt you use tone for other instruments too?

-------------------------

iammane | 2019-07-13 16:07:55 UTC | #25

Because it depends on the instrument. All instruments used ‚Äúshape‚Äù and ‚Äútone‚Äù which really were just labels for whatever macro was actually controlled (chorus, attack, glide etc). It varied by sound.

I have no idea what ‚Äútone‚Äù and ‚Äúshape‚Äù mean in their existing context... still pretty ambiguous.

