Antbrick | 2019-09-12 10:59:33 UTC | #49

Hey guys I have a sample that I‚Äôm trying to edit. It‚Äôs in reverse but there are some clicking noises from the hi hat and snares that‚Äôs originally on the track that I wanted to try and edit out or fix up in a way where you just hear the beat without the clicks. Any tips or assistance would be greatly appreciated.

-------------------------

iammane | 2019-09-12 11:05:58 UTC | #50

There's nothing native to Auxy that's gonna help there. I think Audiocopy by Retronyms has some basic editing functions, it's free. A really great swiss army knife of audio editing is Audioshare, the dev is great, it's 5 bucks but it's paid for itself over and over for me over all these years. 

If you're talking about trying to clean up content in the *middle* of the sample (ie not just trimming) that's gonna be pretty difficult. Maybe with some creative filtering, but it will effect the character of the sound.

-------------------------

blakkaz | 2019-09-12 11:13:41 UTC | #51

Audiocopy should work for your use case.

